# Performance Optimization & Best Practices

## Frontend Performance Optimization

### React Performance Patterns
Follow established patterns for optimal React performance:

```jsx
// Use React.memo for expensive components
const ExpensiveComponent = React.memo(({ data, onAction }) => {
  // Component logic
  return <div>{/* Component JSX */}</div>;
});

// Use useMemo for expensive calculations
const ComponentWithExpensiveCalculation = ({ items }) => {
  const sortedItems = useMemo(() => {
    return items.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
  }, [items]);
  
  return (
    <div>
      {sortedItems.map(item => (
        <Item key={item.id} item={item} />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};

// Use useCallback for stable function references
const ComponentWithStableFunctions = ({ onItemClick }) => {
  const handleItemClick = useCallback((item) => {
    onItemClick(item);
  }, [onItemClick]);
  
  return (
    <div>
      {/* Component content */}
    </div>
  );
};
```

### Code Splitting & Lazy Loading
Follow the established pattern in `src/App.jsx`:

```jsx
// Lazy load page components for better performance
const DashboardPage = React.lazy(() => import('./pages/DashboardPage'));
const CustomersPage = React.lazy(() => import('./pages/CustomersPage'));
const OrdersPage = React.lazy(() => import('./pages/orders/OrdersPage'));

// Use with Suspense for loading states
<React.Suspense fallback={<PageLoading text="جاري تحميل الصفحة..." />}>
  <Routes>
    <Route path="/" element={<DashboardPage />} />
    <Route path="/customers" element={<CustomersPage />} />
    <Route path="/orders" element={<OrdersPage />} />
  </Routes>
</React.Suspense>
```

### Bundle Optimization
Optimize bundle size and loading performance:

```javascript
// Dynamic imports for conditional features
const loadFeature = async (featureName) => {
  const module = await import(`./features/${featureName}`);
  return module.default;
};

// Route-based code splitting
const routes = {
  dashboard: () => import('./pages/DashboardPage'),
  customers: () => import('./pages/CustomersPage'),
  orders: () => import('./pages/orders/OrdersPage'),
  analytics: () => import('./pages/analytics/AnalyticsPage')
};

// Load routes dynamically
const loadRoute = async (routeName) => {
  if (routes[routeName]) {
    const module = await routes[routeName]();
    return module.default;
  }
  throw new Error(`Route ${routeName} not found`);
};
```

